properties.description: The zip code associated with the bad alias.

collections.name: congress_representatives

properties.name: congress_rep_id
properties.description: The unique identifier for the congress representative, often representing state and district (e.g., 'NY-1').

properties.name: first_name
properties.description: The first name of the congress representative.

properties.name: last_name
properties.description: The last name of the congress representative.

properties.name: cid
properties.description: The unique identifier (CID) for the congress representative.

properties.name: party
properties.description: The political party of the representative.

properties.name: state
properties.description: The full name of the state that the representative is from.

properties.name: abbreviation
properties.description: The two-letter abbreviation of the state.

properties.name: house
properties.description: The house (e.g., House of Representatives, Senate) that the representative is from.

properties.name: district
properties.description: The ID of the district that the representative represents.

extra semantic info.context: The state is divided into different districts. The districts under the same state will be numbered uniformly.
extra semantic info.NA_meaning: 'NA' means that the state is not divided into districts.

properties.name: land_area
properties.description: The land area of the district represented by the congress member.

collections.description: This collection contains information about US Congress representatives.

collections.name: state

properties.name: abbreviation
properties.description: The two-letter abbreviation of the state name.

properties.name: name

collections.description: This collection provides a list of US states and their abbreviations.

collections.name: zip_congress

collections.name: zip_data

properties.name: zip_code
properties.description: The zip code of the postal point.

properties.name: city
properties.description: The primary city name for the postal point.

properties.name: state
properties.description: The two-letter abbreviation of the state where the city is located.

properties.name: multi_county
properties.description: Indicates whether the zip code spans across multiple counties.

extra semantic info.definition: Consisting of or involving multiple counties.

properties.name: type_
properties.description: The type of the postal point (e.g., 'Post Office', 'Unique Post Office').

properties.name: organization
properties.description: The organization to which the postal point belongs.

extra semantic info.no_data_meaning: 'No data' indicates the postal point is not affiliated with any organization.

properties.name: time_zone
properties.description: The time zone of the postal point location.

properties.name: daylight_savings
properties.description: Indicates whether the location implements daylight saving time.

extra semantic info.definition: Daylight saving is the practice of advancing clocks (typically by one hour) during warmer months so that darkness falls at a later clock time. As a result, there is one 23-hour day in late winter or early spring and one 25-hour day in autumn.

properties.name: latitude
properties.description: The latitude coordinate of the postal point location.

properties.name: longitude
properties.description: The longitude coordinate of the postal point location.

properties.name: elevation
properties.description: The elevation of the postal point location in feet.

properties.name: state_fips
properties.description: The state-level FIPS code for the postal point's location.

properties.name: county_fips
properties.description: The county-level FIPS code for the postal point's location.

extra semantic info.context: FIPS codes are numbers that uniquely identify geographic areas. The number of digits in FIPS codes varies depending on the level of geography.

properties.name: region
properties.description: The geographic region where the postal point is located.

properties.name: division
properties.description: The division of the organization to which the postal point belongs.

extra semantic info.no_data_meaning: 'No data' indicates the postal point is not affiliated with any organization or the organization has no division.

properties.name: population_2020
properties.description: The population of the residential area in 2020.

properties.name: population_2010
properties.description: The population of the residential area in 2010.

properties.name: households
properties.description: The total number of households in the residential area.

properties.name: avg_house_value
properties.description: The average house value in the residential area.

properties.name: avg_income_per_household
properties.description: The average income per household in the residential area.

properties.name: persons_per_household
properties.description: The average number of persons per household in the residential area.

properties.name: white_population
properties.description: The population of white people in the residential area.

properties.name: black_population
properties.description: The population of black people in the residential area.

properties.name: hispanic_population
properties.description: The population of Hispanic people in the residential area.

properties.name: asian_population
properties.description: The population of Asian people in the residential area.

properties.name: american_indian_population
properties.description: The population of American Indian people in the residential area.

properties.name: hawaiian_population
properties.description: The population of Hawaiian people in the residential area.

properties.name: other_population
properties.description: The population of other races in the residential area.

properties.name: male_population
properties.description: The total male population in the residential area.

properties.name: female_population
properties.description: The total female population in the residential area.

properties.name: median_age
properties.description: The median age of the overall population in the residential area.

properties.name: male_median_age
properties.description: The median age of the male population in the residential area.

properties.name: female_median_age
properties.description: The median age of the female population in the residential area.

properties.name: residential_mailboxes
properties.description: The number of residential mailboxes in the area.

properties.name: business_mailboxes
properties.description: The number of business mailboxes in the area.

properties.name: total_delivery_receptacles
properties.description: The total number of delivery receptacles (residential and business) in the area.

properties.name: businesses
properties.description: The total number of businesses operating in the residential area.

properties.name: _1st_quarter_payroll
properties.description: The total wages reported in the first quarter payroll report for the residential area.

properties.name: annual_payroll
properties.description: The total wages reported in the annual payroll report for the residential area.

properties.name: employees
properties.description: The total number of employees in the residential area.

properties.name: water_area
properties.description: The water area in square miles for the residential area.

properties.name: land_area
properties.description: The land area in square miles for the residential area.

properties.name: single_family_delivery_units
properties.description: The number of single-family delivery units in the residential area.

extra semantic info.definition: A single-family unit accommodates only one family or tenant at a time.

properties.name: multi_family_delivery_units
properties.description: The number of multi-family delivery units in the residential area.

extra semantic info.definition: Multi-family units are larger and can accommodate more than one tenant or multiple families at a time.

properties.name: total_beneficiaries
properties.description: The total number of beneficiaries of postal services or social security in the area.

properties.name: retired_workers
properties.description: The number of retired workers receiving benefits in the residential area.

properties.name: disabled_workers
properties.description: The number of disabled workers receiving benefits in the residential area.

properties.name: parents_and_widowed
properties.description: The number of parents and widowed individuals receiving benefits in the residential area.

properties.name: spouses
properties.description: The number of spouses receiving benefits in the residential area.

properties.name: children
properties.description: The number of children receiving benefits in the residential area.

properties.name: over_65
properties.description: The number of people aged over 65 in the residential area.

properties.name: monthly_benefits_all
properties.description: The total amount of all monthly benefit payments in the residential area (in USD).

properties.name: monthly_benefits_retired_workers
properties.description: The total monthly benefit payments specifically for retired workers (in USD).

properties.name: monthly_benefits_widowed
properties.description: The total monthly benefit payments specifically for widowed individuals (in USD).

properties.name: cbsa
properties.description: The Core Based Statistical Area (CBSA) code associated with the zip code.

collections.description: This collection contains comprehensive demographic, geographic, and economic data for various zip codes.

extra semantic info.gender_ratio_derivation: Gender ratio in the residential area can be calculated as male_population / female_population if female_population is not zero.
extra semantic info.payroll_reports_context: Employers must submit periodic payroll reports to the Internal Revenue Service and state taxing authority. These reports are used to convey wage information.
extra semantic info.aging_population_analysis: The number of people over 65 (elders) can be compared to children. A higher ratio of over_65 / children suggests a more serious aging population issue.
